We analyse Paul Bosman, fund manager at PSG Asset Management.If someone came to you tomorrow with R100m to invest in just one company, which would it be?Brookfield Asset Management.Which talent would you most like to possess?Is hair a talent?What was your first job?Working as a call centre agent in Edinburg.What&rsquo;s your biggest regret?Only having a student&rsquo;s disposable income when Capitec and EOH were trading below R2/share.What is the worst investment mistake you have made?Love birds.What&rsquo;s the best investment you&rsquo;ve ever made?PSG Group.If you found a lottery ticket tomorrow that had won US$100m, what would you do?I&rsquo;d buy new shoes, Eben Sadie&rsquo;s 2018 harvest and a couple of Berkshire Hathaway A shares (just because I could). And then I would ask my colleagues to recommend a unit trust.What&rsquo;s your favourite song?"The Boxer".On what occasions do you lie?When I&rsquo;ve taken something that is not mine.Your greatest extravagance? Going to places where I have to pay in euros.Name a place you&rsquo;ve been to that lived up to the hype.Muizenberg when the wind is north.If you could fix one thing in SA today, what would it be?We need a better president.